lines.text: READ RIGHT
INSTITUTE
SYED TAIMOOR BUKHARI
Date :..
JTL
ITI
JFD
It has, undeniably, wisely phrased
that it needs education to break free females from
blind obedience. Any one who is educated,
questions, thinks, rationalizes and only
then make an action. Any task they perform
is backed by national calculation and
estimation of the consequences of following
that command Same is the case with
Women. When female are educated, they
do not act blindly or follow mindlessly.
They question and rationalize and
only than decide on whether to comply
or not. By enlarging the femal mind is
by virtue of educating them makes them
better not only for their own good but
also for the entire society. Unfortunately,
there are various social, economic,
political and traditional hindrances
in way of educating the females. They
make more than 50% of the world
population yet their plight gets crushed
intiname of traditions and cultures-
Owing to reasons, females become
bound to obey blindly. They suffer
socially, politically and economically
and generational cycles of women
